-- England Leads Australia by 282 Runs in First Ashes Cricket Test
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-07-13T12:05:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-13/england-leads-australia-by-282-runs-in-first-ashes-cricket-test.html
England leads Australia by 282 runs
at lunch on day four of the opening Test of the Ashes cricket
series.  Ian Bell  scored 109 as England was dismissed for 375 in its
second innings in Nottingham, setting the visitors a record
target of 311 to win. Bell shared a seventh-wicket stand of 138
with  Stuart Broad , who made 65.  Australia is 28-0 as Shane Watson scored 18 and Chris
Rogers made 10. No team has ever chased more than 284 to win at
Test at Trent Bridge.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  